{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 11:08:10.476406", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary\\n- Overall health: Normal. End-to-end connectivity between hosts is working with 0% loss and low latency. All EBGP sessions across leaves, spines, and the super-spine are established. Routing tables contain the expected prefixes and next-hops. No anomalies impacting reachability were detected.\\n\\nTests Performed\\n- Host reachability matrix across all hosts.\\n- FRR BGP status (show ip bgp summary) on: leaf_router_0_0, leaf_router_0_1, spine_router_0_0, spine_router_0_1, super_spine_router_0.\\n- Routing tables (show ip route) on the same routers.\\n\\nKey Findings\\n\\n1) Host reachability\\n- pc_0_0 → pc_0_1: 0% loss, avg RTT ~3.5 ms.\\n- pc_0_1 → pc_0_0: 0% loss, avg RTT ~1.5 ms.\\n- Interpretation: End-to-end L3 connectivity is intact; no packet loss or abnormal latency observed.\\n\\n2) BGP session status (all Established)\\n- leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200): Peers up with spine_router_0_0 (172.16.0.4, AS 65100) and spine_router_0_1 (172.16.0.8, AS 65101); receives 1 prefix from each; sends 2.\\n- leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201): Peers up with spine_router_0_0 (172.16.0.6, AS 65100) and spine_router_0_1 (172.16.0.10, AS 65101); receives 1 prefix from each; sends 2.\\n- spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100): Peers up with super_spine_router_0 (172.16.0.0, AS 65000), and both leaves; receives 1 prefix each from the leaves; 0 from super-spine (explained below).\\n- spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101): Peers up with super_spine_router_0 (172.16.0.2, AS 65000), and both leaves; receives 2 prefixes from each neighbor (explained below).\\n- super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000): Peers up with both spines; receives 2 prefixes from each; route selection prefers spine_router_0_0 for both /24s.\\n\\n3) Routing correctness and path selection\\n- leaf_router_0_0: \\n  - Connected: 10.0.0.0/24 on eth2.\\n  - Remote: 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.4 (spine_router_0_0).\\n- leaf_router_0_1:\\n  - Connected: 10.0.1.0/24 on eth2.\\n  - Remote: 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.6 (spine_router_0_0).\\n- spine_router_0_0:\\n  - 10.0.0.0/24 via leaf_router_0_0 (172.16.0.5).\\n  - 10.0.1.0/24 via leaf_router_0_1 (172.16.0.7).\\n- spine_router_0_1:\\n  - 10.0.0.0/24 via leaf_router_0_0 (172.16.0.9).\\n  - 10.0.1.0/24 via leaf_router_0_1 (172.16.0.11).\\n- super_spine_router_0:\\n  - Selects spine_router_0_0 (172.16.0.1) as best for both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24.\\n\\n4) Notable behaviors (non-fault observations)\\n- Asymmetric prefix reception at spines from the super-spine:\\n  - spine_router_0_0 shows 0 prefixes received from the super-spine; spine_router_0_1 shows 2. This is expected:\\n    - The super-spine’s best path for both leaf prefixes currently points to spine_router_0_0. Advertising those best paths back to spine_router_0_0 would include AS 65100 in the AS-Path, which the receiving spine rejects due to AS loop prevention. Conversely, spine_router_0_1 can accept them (AS-Path does not include its own AS).\\n- ECMP is not in use:\\n  - Leaves select a single spine for the remote /24 (no multipath), and the super-spine selects spine_router_0_0 for both /24s. Consequently, inter-leaf traffic currently transits spine_router_0_0 in both directions. This is a deterministic best-path outcome and not a malfunction.\\n\\nConclusions\\n- Anomaly detection: No operational anomalies detected. All BGP adjacencies are Established, RIBs/FIBs contain expected entries, and host connectivity is normal with 0% loss.\\n- Fault localization: No faulty device identified; all routers and links used per the topology behave as expected.\\n- Root cause (for observed asymmetries): Normal BGP best-path selection without multipath and AS-path loop prevention explain the asymmetric prefix reception and single-spine usage for inter-subnet traffic. This is an expected control-plane behavior under the current policy and does not indicate a fault., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='8f0a1c54-54fe-4864-b082-92d8b49c24e3'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
